{
  "text": "Proof. We have [e 1 , e 2 ] = \u2212 tan \u03b8h 3 22 e 2 because of (9). Thus, if m is a nonvanishing smooth function on M satisfying (16), then we have [e 1 , me 2 ] = 0. Therefore, there exists a local coordinate system (s, t) such that e 1 = \u2202 s and e 2 = 1 m \u2202 t . Thus, the induced metric of M is as given in [CITATION_1] . Now, we are ready to obtain the classification theorem.",
